      "id": 1,
      "text": "South Miami Heights grew around a post office moved by the U.S. government, and the community was named Larkins after its postmaster.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.southmiamifl.gov/217/Citys-History"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "After the 1906 Florida East Coast Railway extension, Larkins opened the first grocery and general supply store in the area.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3,
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.floridavisiting.com/list/south-miami/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 2001, South Miami was honored as an All‑America City for its civic participation and community cooperation.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.floridavisiting.com/list/south-miami/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "South Miami has kept much of its historic character while evolving into a convenient base for dining, shopping, and medical services.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9
